releases.body:
# Mac version

The dmg file provides the PMUI app like a typical mac program. An uninstaller is provided in the dmg for removing PMUI and all PMUI-related user data for the user that executes the uninstaller.

# Windows version

The installer file installs PMUI like a typical windows program. Uninstall via the control panel will remove PMUI as well as PMUI-related data from the user which runs the uninstaller.

- change copy on settings page
- populate periods on initial load and every 10 mins
- extend devtool to create very old sysevent
- time spent idle bar charts
- pie chart with real data
- update mac and windows binaries

- Server connection config window (raven) always on top
- Mac: Check authorization during power settings query method (no "authorize" button on reload)
- Mac: Sliders will now handle mid-values (instead of just rendering nothing!) in case it was set to something like 7 minutes in system settings

- Full Mac support
- Improved security when communicating with server (TLS and auto-generated token)
- App chrome and implemented pages are all fully functional and styled

- added partial mac support (monitoring, but not setting, due to root privilege requirement)
- fixed issue with period analysis and chart data

- Chart auto updating
- Styled app
- Windowless/Monitor [feature](https://github.com/Calit2-UCI/pm-shell/blob/28ee4d917a05355cd7df1e6842f00d710eb87d61/README.md#toggling-windowless-mode)
